What is a Commercial Hybrid UAV?
Commercial hybrid UAVs combine electric motors with internal‑combustion engines to deliver a synergistic powertrain. The electric motor provides silent, low‑noise operation during cruise, while the combustion engine supplies robust thrust for take‑off, climb, and sustained endurance. This dual‑propulsion architecture offers a practical transition for operators moving toward fully electric fleets, enhancing payload capacity and mission versatility.
